      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_0_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "How much home can I afford?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_0_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "Many people start by determining what they can afford as a monthly payment. A common starting point is to calculate 25% of your gross monthly income to help determine a manageable monthly mortgage payment.  Learn more about determining your monthly payment Wells Fargo home price range calculator "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_1_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "What parts of my finances does a mortgage lender review?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_1_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "A lender will check your credit score and history, your debt-to-income ratio, which is a measurement of the amount of debt you have compared to your income, and take a general look at how much money you have in checking and savings accounts in order to be confident you’ll be able to pay for your mortgage, taxes, and other costs associated with buying a home.  Learn more about your finances and how they impact buying a home Read tips on establishing and building credit "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_2_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "What is the minimum down payment for conventional, FHA, and VA loans?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_2_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "Wells Fargo offers several low down payment options, including conventional loans (those not backed by a government agency). Conventional fixed-rate loans are available with a down payment as low as 3%.Opens a modal dialog for footnote 6  Talk with a home mortgage consultant about loan amount, loan type, property type, income, first-time homebuyer, and homebuyer education requirements to discuss eligibility.  FHA loans are available with as little as 3.5% down.  FHA loans have the benefit of a low down payment, but consider all costs involved, including up-front and long-term mortgage insurance and all fees. Ask your home mortgage consultant to help you compare the overall costs of all your home financing options.  VA loans Up to 100% financing may be available on VA loans for qualified borrowers.Opens a modal dialog for footnote 7"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_3_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question",
              "name": "What other costs are part of my mortgage?",
              "acceptedAnswer": [
                {
                  "@type": "Answer",
                  "@id": "https://www.wellsfargo.com/mortgage/#Highlight20250910145046693-27495_3_CollectionPage_mainEntity_FAQPage_mainEntity_Question_acceptedAnswer_Answer",
                  "text": "Your monthly mortgage payment typically will include principal and interest on the mortgage, as well as homeowners insurance and property taxes if your mortgage payment includes escrow. Depending on your down payment and loan type, you may also have to pay private mortgage insurance as part of your monthly mortgage payment.  Learn more about the components of a mortgage payment Learn more about escrow "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
